<section id="Domain">
  <title>Domain</title>

  <para>Identifies the topic, theme, or subject of the content in scope. See <olink
      targetdoc="../xliff21.xml" targetptr="ITS20">[ITS]</olink>
    <ulink url="http://www.w3.org/TR/its20/#domain">Domain</ulink> for
    details.</para>
  <itemizedlist>
    <title>Processing Requirements</title>
    <listitem><para><firstterm>Writers</firstterm>
        <glossterm>must</glossterm> use the attribute <olink
          targetdoc="../../attributes/itsm/itsm_domains.xml" targetptr="itsm_domains"
            ><code>itsm:domains</code></olink> to express the <olink targetdoc="../xliff21.xml"
          targetptr="ITS20">[ITS]</olink>
        <ulink url="http://www.w3.org/TR/its20/#domain">Domain</ulink> data category in
          <firstterm>XLIFF Documents</firstterm>.</para></listitem>

  </itemizedlist>
  <warning>
    <para>Please note that the <link linkend="Domain">Domain metadata category</link> uses the
      <olink targetdoc="../attributes/itsm/itsm_domains.xml" targetptr="itsm_domains"><code>itsm:domains</code></olink> attribute that
      belongs to the <code>urn:oasis:names:tc:xliff:itsm:2.1</code> namespace (prefixed with
        <code>itsm:</code>) and not to the <code>https://www.w3.org/2005/11/its/</code> (prefixed
      with <code>its</code>) as most of the other attributes described in this module.</para>
  </warning>


  <section id="Domain_Structural">
    <title>Structural Elements</title>


    <example>
      <title>Extraction of Domain at structural levels</title>

    <para>Original:</para>

      <programlisting>
&lt;!doctype html&gt;
&lt;html lang="en"&gt;
  &lt;head&gt;
    &lt;meta charset="utf-8"&gt;
    &lt;title&gt;Data Category: Domain&lt;/title&gt;
    &lt;script type="application/its+xml"&gt;
      &lt;its:rules xmlns:its="<ulink url="http://www.w3.org/2005/11/its">http://www.w3.org/2005/11/its</ulink>" version="2.0"
          xmlns:h="<ulink url="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml</ulink>"&gt;
        &lt;its:domainRule selector="//h:*[@class='dom1']"
            domainPointer="./@class" domainMapping="dom1 domain1" /&gt;
      &lt;/its:rules&gt;
    &lt;/script&gt;
  &lt;/head&gt;
  &lt;body&gt;
    &lt;p class="dom1"&gt;Text in the domain domain1&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;
 </programlisting>


    <para>Extraction:</para>


      <programlisting>
...
&lt;unit id='2' itsm:domains="domain1">
  &lt;segment>
    &lt;source&gt;Text in the domain domain1&lt;/source>
  &lt;/segment>
&lt;/unit>
...
</programlisting>
   </example>



  </section>
  <section id="Domain_Inline">
    <title>Inline Elements</title>
    <para> Use <code><olink targetdoc="../elements/inline/mrk.xml" targetptr="mrk"
        >&lt;mrk></olink></code> or an <code><olink targetdoc="../elements/inline/sm.xml"
          targetptr="sm">&lt;sm/></olink></code> / <code><olink
          targetdoc="../elements/inline/em.xml" targetptr="em">&lt;em/></olink></code> pair with the
        <olink targetdoc="../../attributes/itsm/itsm_domains.xml" targetptr="itsm_domains"
          ><code>itsm:domains</code></olink> attribute set.</para>
    <para>See the <link linkend="domainsAnnotation">ITS Domain Annotation</link> for the normative
      usage description on inline markers.</para>

  </section>

  <section id="domainsAnnotation">
    <title>ITS Domain Annotation</title>
    <para>This is used to express inline the <olink targetdoc="../xliff21.xml" targetptr="ITS20"
        >[ITS]</olink>
      <ulink url="http://www.w3.org/TR/its20/#domain">Domain</ulink> data category. </para>
    <para>Usage:</para>
    <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
      <listitem>
        <para>The <olink targetdoc="../../attributes/id.xml" targetptr="id"
          ><code>id</code></olink> attribute is <glossterm>required</glossterm>.</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>The <olink targetdoc="../../attributes/itsm/itsm_domains.xml" targetptr="itsm_domains"
              ><code>itsm:domains</code></olink> attribute is
          <glossterm>required</glossterm>.</para>
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
        <para>The <olink targetdoc="../../attributes/type.xml" targetptr="type"
          ><code>type</code></olink> attribute is <glossterm>optional</glossterm> and set to
          <code>its:generic</code>.</para>

      </listitem>


      <listitem>
        <para>The <olink targetdoc="../../attributes/translate.xml" targetptr="translate"
          ><code>translate</code></olink> attribute is <glossterm>optional</glossterm>.</para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
    <example>
      <title>Extraction of Domain metadata on inline elements</title>

      <para>Original:</para>
      <programlisting>
&lt;!doctype html&gt;
&lt;html lang="en"&gt;
  &lt;head&gt;
    &lt;meta charset="utf-8"&gt;
    &lt;title&gt;Data Category: Domain&lt;/title&gt;
    &lt;script type="application/its+xml"&gt;
      &lt;its:rules xmlns:its="<ulink url="http://www.w3.org/2005/11/its">http://www.w3.org/2005/11/its</ulink>" version="2.0"
          xmlns:h="<ulink url="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml</ulink>"&gt;
        &lt;its:domainRule selector="//h:*[@class='dom1']"
            domainPointer="./@class" domainMapping="dom1 domain1" /&gt;
      &lt;/its:rules&gt;
    &lt;/script&gt;
  &lt;/head&gt;
  &lt;body&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;Span of text &lt;span class="dom1"&gt;in the domain domain1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;
 </programlisting>
      <para>Extraction:</para>
      <programlisting>
...
&lt;unit id="1"&gt;
  &lt;segment&gt;
    &lt;source&gt;Span of text &lt;pc id="1"&gt;&lt;mrk id="m1" type="its:generic"
        itsm:domains="domain1" &gt;in the domain domain1&lt;/mrk&gt;&lt;/pc&gt;&lt;/source&gt;
  &lt;/segment&gt;
&lt;/unit&gt;
...
</programlisting>
    </example>
  </section>

